  "147": {
    "text": "THE magic line. <code>vmap(forward_single, in_axes=(None, 0, 0))</code> creates a batched version automatically. <code>None</code> means params are shared (not batched); <code>0</code> means batch along the first axis for inputs and masks. This one line replaces all of lab 04's manual batch reshaping.",
    "hash": "33d95e5b"
  },
  "150": {
    "text": "Batched loss function. The forward pass is already batched thanks to <code>vmap</code>.",
    "hash": "ee5f8a69"
  },
  "155": {
    "text": "Call the vmap'd forward \u2014 returns (B, T, V) logits from (B, T) inputs.",
    "hash": "6dbc0b8f"
  },
  "156": {
    "text": "Log-softmax for numerical stability.",
    "hash": "557f67de"
  },
  "157": {
    "text": "Unpack batch, time, vocab dimensions.",
    "hash": "6fd1445a"
  },
  "159": {
    "text": "Gather log-probs for target tokens using advanced indexing. Fancy indexing: for each batch and position, grab the log-prob of the correct target.",
    "hash": "630d9e02"
  },
  "161": {
    "text": "Zero out padding positions so they don't affect the loss.",
    "hash": "04bbd9c3"
  },
  "162": {
    "text": "Average only over real (non-padded) tokens. Dividing by <code>sum(target_mask)</code> ensures short sequences aren't penalized relative to long ones.",
    "hash": "3ed652fa"
  },
